1
00:01:26,110 --> 00:01:34,990
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:37,820
[Episode 12]

3
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:24,500
Just because you have a few bucks,

4
00:02:25,130 --> 00:02:26,790
you're starting to get cocky?

5
00:02:28,090 --> 00:02:29,900
A big horse is worth money,

6
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,360
but a person with a big ego

7
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:32,930
is worthless.

8
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:33,960
Get to work!

9
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:43,930
"Is she pretty?"

10
00:02:45,690 --> 00:02:48,240
Dong'er lit a cigarette and asked.

11
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,780
Wu Xiaoshuai answered...

12
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:54,460
"Average."

13
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:56,520
Dong'er blew out a puff of smoke.

14
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:57,430
She smiled and said...

15
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:57,970
They...

16
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:01,210
"Don't be nervous.

17
00:03:02,130 --> 00:03:04,250
I'm not trying to seduce you."

18
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,450
What are you doing?

19
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:07,680
What are you doing?

20
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,010
I... Master, I am trying

21
00:03:09,180 --> 00:03:10,410
to get into the character's head.

22
00:03:10,410 --> 00:03:11,030
Look at us.

23
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:11,690
With this back and forth dialogue,

24
00:03:11,690 --> 00:03:12,400
the romantic tension

25
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,930
just builds up, doesn't it?

26
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,060
Who is your master?

27
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,930
Who is getting romantic with you?

28
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:17,910
You are ruining

29
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:19,190
the atmosphere like this.

30
00:03:19,190 --> 00:03:20,020
I was thinking

31
00:03:20,430 --> 00:03:21,240
that this is the first time

32
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:21,900
the two of them are sharing

33
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:22,960
a confined space.

34
00:03:23,090 --> 00:03:23,400
Right.

35
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,500
If you keep chatting like this,

36
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:25,710
it... it will be hard to end well.

37
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:26,500
Well, look.

38
00:03:26,870 --> 00:03:27,470
Dong'er

39
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:29,400
has a lot of pride.

40
00:03:29,579 --> 00:03:31,500
She would never hand the initiative

41
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:32,860
over to Wu Xiaoshuai.

42
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:34,780
Sometimes, to break

43
00:03:34,780 --> 00:03:35,960
the ambiguous atmosphere,

44
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,250
the best way is to

45
00:03:37,970 --> 00:03:39,030
make things clear.

46
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:41,020
I think

47
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:42,430
that you forgot our rules

48
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,810
in the blink of an eye.

49
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:45,460
Put your hand out.

50
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,180
Hand out!

51
00:03:46,430 --> 00:03:47,650
Hurry, hand out!

52
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:54,370
Forget it, forget it.

53
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:59,120
Water. Water. Give me some water.

54
00:03:59,120 --> 00:03:59,579
Water.

55
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:01,640
Slow down. Slow down.

56
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,250
Slowly.

57
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:03,060
Good.

58
00:04:04,780 --> 00:04:06,780
Did you learn your lesson this time?

59
00:04:07,690 --> 00:04:09,020
Sit down. Keep writing.

60
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:10,390
Keep writing.

61
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:22,460
[Registration Room]

62
00:04:15,430 --> 00:04:17,800
You want me to open the door at this hour?

63
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:18,600
I'm really sorry.

64
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,920
The rooster hasn't even crowed yet.

65
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:20,250
Yeah.

66
00:04:20,660 --> 00:04:21,930
What kind of job is this?

67
00:04:21,930 --> 00:04:23,060
Sorry to bother you.

68
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:24,530
It's a bothersome job.

69
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:27,830
Here, bro.

70
00:04:27,980 --> 00:04:28,890
Take this.

71
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,360
I'm always troubling you.

72
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,690
Take it and have a smoke.

73
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:32,870
No need.

74
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:34,150
I'm just doing my job.

75
00:04:35,159 --> 00:04:36,190
If you need anything, just say the word.

76
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:37,060
What do you mean "just doing your job"?

77
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:37,920
I can't always be bothering you.

78
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:38,310
Morning.

79
00:04:38,310 --> 00:04:39,770
Another night owl is back.

80
00:04:41,510 --> 00:04:42,750
Roommate, roommate!

81
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:49,810
You're up even earlier than me.

82
00:04:49,810 --> 00:04:51,300
Where are you coming back from?

83
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,310
Writing scripts

84
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:53,530
has no schedule to it.

85
00:04:54,570 --> 00:04:55,570
Writing scripts?

86
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:57,620
So you're an artist?

87
00:04:57,890 --> 00:04:59,090
Something like that.

88
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,330
Must be making a ton of money, right?

89
00:05:00,330 --> 00:05:01,450
I don't make money.

90
00:05:01,450 --> 00:05:02,810
I'm studying with a mentor.

91
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:03,540
Look at you.

92
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:05,460
You really don't make money?

93
00:05:06,690 --> 00:05:07,480
If you don't make money,

94
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,280
why are you so happy all the time?

95
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:11,270
I thought you were making a fortune.

96
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:12,750
I don't get your industry.

97
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,720
I thought you artists

98
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:15,360
just messed around

99
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,230
and the money rolled in.

100
00:05:16,230 --> 00:05:16,810
No, no.

101
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,300
No one has it easy, right?

102
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,890
But you're up early
and back late every day.

103
00:05:19,890 --> 00:05:20,690
What do you do?

104
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:23,980
Let me tell you.

105
00:05:24,070 --> 00:05:26,200
My company sent me here to Beijing.

106
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,250
The dorm

107
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:28,360
isn't ready for me yet.

108
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,720
Otherwise, I wouldn't be staying here.

109
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:32,050
The work started before my dorm was ready.

110
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:33,040
They want me to buy

111
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:35,100
train tickets for the whole company.

112
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:36,830
Let me tell you.

113
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:38,720
Just to earn this little subsidy,

114
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:39,720
I have to get up this early

115
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,010
and queue up to buy tickets for people.

116
00:05:41,010 --> 00:05:42,010
That's not easy either.

117
00:05:42,010 --> 00:05:43,810
But at least you make some money.

118
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:47,150
Let me ask you something.

119
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:48,930
Is this always your schedule?

120
00:05:49,810 --> 00:05:51,610
My schedule isn't that regular.

121
00:05:52,740 --> 00:05:54,270
I don't mean anything else.

122
00:05:54,430 --> 00:05:55,800
We can cooperate.

123
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,159
You can make some extra cash.

124
00:05:58,770 --> 00:05:59,970
Let me put it this way.

125
00:06:00,370 --> 00:06:01,540
Getting up early for me

126
00:06:01,540 --> 00:06:02,920
is a huge struggle.

127
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:05,420
Since you're up at this time anyway,

128
00:06:05,420 --> 00:06:07,000
you can just go to the station

129
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,330
and grab tickets for me.

130
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:09,540
I won't let you do it for free.

131
00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:10,980
I'll give you 50 a trip.

132
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:11,980
Deal?

133
00:06:12,930 --> 00:06:14,060
Fifty a trip?

134
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:19,000
But my teacher

135
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,040
sleeps on and off.

136
00:06:20,060 --> 00:06:21,740
His schedule is very irregular.

137
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:23,490
I'm afraid I'll hold you up.

138
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,610
I thought you found the pay too low.

139
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:27,770
I understand.

140
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:29,050
How about this.

141
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,950
When you get a regular schedule,

142
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,120
let me know.

143
00:06:32,690 --> 00:06:34,640
I'll save this job for you.

144
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:35,200
Okay?

145
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:36,430
Okay.

146
00:06:37,190 --> 00:06:37,740
I'm off.

147
00:06:39,130 --> 00:06:39,830
Thanks.

148
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:40,860
Don't mention it.

149
00:06:40,860 --> 00:06:42,860
We're roommates. Don't mention it.

150
00:06:44,770 --> 00:06:46,970
With this temporary residence permit,

151
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:48,950
we count as Beijingers now.

152
00:06:49,810 --> 00:06:51,310
At most, we're...

153
00:06:51,430 --> 00:06:53,330
temporary Beijingers.

154
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:55,960
Don't you know how to round up?

155
00:06:56,060 --> 00:06:57,540
You can round this up?

156
00:06:57,570 --> 00:06:58,220
Why not?

157
00:06:58,870 --> 00:06:59,800
Let me see yours.

158
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:05,510
You look quite proper.

159
00:07:06,540 --> 00:07:08,030
But it didn't capture your charm.

160
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:12,560
[Name: Xu Shengli]

161
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:09,830
What charm?

162
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:15,190
An adorkable charm.

163
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:17,560
[Name: Xu Shengli]

164
00:07:17,860 --> 00:07:19,240
Who's a dork?

165
00:07:31,570 --> 00:07:31,920
By the way,

166
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,450
how are your classes going?

167
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:36,690
My teacher

168
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:38,830
has a weird temper.

169
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,320
He's a bit hard to please.

170
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,420
Maybe you didn't do something right.

171
00:07:43,420 --> 00:07:45,040
What didn't I do right?

172
00:07:45,930 --> 00:07:46,740
Every day,

173
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,630
he talks and I write,

174
00:07:48,630 --> 00:07:49,630
I cook and he eats,

175
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:50,950
I read and he scolds me.

176
00:07:50,950 --> 00:07:52,130
I've been diligent,

177
00:07:52,130 --> 00:07:53,540
steady, and meticulous.

178
00:07:55,130 --> 00:07:56,190
You can cook?

179
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:00,530
Wait, what do you mean?

180
00:08:01,330 --> 00:08:02,500
You're mocking me.

181
00:08:02,770 --> 00:08:04,120
I may not be good at it,

182
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,250
but I can still do it.

183
00:08:05,770 --> 00:08:06,890
With your skills?

184
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:08,420
My skills

185
00:08:08,450 --> 00:08:09,720
were learned from you.

186
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:11,040
I definitely cook better than you.

187
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:11,560
Fine.

188
00:08:11,740 --> 00:08:12,600
You're better.

189
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:15,950
Could it be that the problem

190
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:17,080
lies in the food?

191
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,180
If people don't eat well,

192
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:19,710
they tend to get irritable.

193
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:22,790
I've heard of morning temper,

194
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:24,810
but I've never heard of food temper.

195
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:25,360
He's just eating.

196
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:26,740
How can he get so worked up?

197
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:28,360
Well, that's the extent of my skills.

198
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,360
I can't help it.

199
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:30,260
Learn.

200
00:08:30,450 --> 00:08:31,120
Learn?

201
00:08:31,180 --> 00:08:32,510
Who should I learn from?

202
00:08:35,549 --> 00:08:37,679
Wipe yourself. You got it all over you.

203
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:40,780
Where is your teacher from?

204
00:08:40,909 --> 00:08:41,700
Sichuan.

205
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:53,910
Don't you understand the principle

206
00:08:53,910 --> 00:08:55,510
of catering to one's tastes?

207
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:56,700
Sichuan cuisine?

208
00:08:57,530 --> 00:08:58,150
Sure.

209
00:08:58,530 --> 00:08:59,930
Then I'll learn from you.

210
00:09:00,130 --> 00:09:01,240
I'm from Wenzhou

211
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:03,000
and you want to learn
Sichuan cuisine from me?

212
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,170
Then I'll learn Wenzhou cuisine

213
00:09:04,170 --> 00:09:04,750
from you

214
00:09:04,770 --> 00:09:06,670
and I'll add some chili peppers.
Won't that work?

215
00:09:06,670 --> 00:09:07,210
Fine.

216
00:09:07,460 --> 00:09:07,790
Okay.

217
00:09:11,130 --> 00:09:11,460
Okay.

218
00:09:11,460 --> 00:09:12,750
I'll ask around for you later

219
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:14,570
to see who can cook Sichuan cuisine.

220
00:09:14,570 --> 00:09:14,940
Okay.

221
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:16,680
You're the best.

222
00:09:17,530 --> 00:09:18,330
Really great.

223
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:20,500
How about you?

224
00:09:20,550 --> 00:09:22,150
How's your troupe audition?

225
00:09:26,770 --> 00:09:27,720
Something happened?

226
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,220
Tell me, what went wrong?

227
00:09:29,270 --> 00:09:30,170
Don't ask.

228
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,350
Mr. Zheng paid my tuition fees.

229
00:09:32,430 --> 00:09:33,790
I saved up some money to pay him back,

230
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:34,510
but Mrs. Zheng

231
00:09:34,510 --> 00:09:35,820
caught us right in the act.

232
00:09:35,820 --> 00:09:36,700
Now look what happened.

233
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:38,560
Mr. Zheng got dragged into it too.

234
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,960
If you ask me,

235
00:09:45,650 --> 00:09:46,650
it's not that bad.

236
00:09:48,150 --> 00:09:49,410
I still feel terrible.

237
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:52,050
It puts Mr. Zheng in a tough spot.

238
00:09:52,050 --> 00:09:53,580
If you feel shy,

239
00:09:53,580 --> 00:09:54,580
then don't go.

240
00:09:56,770 --> 00:09:59,100
Don't make me kick you into the lake!

241
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:00,250
Fine.

242
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,890
I'll figure something out for you.

243
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:06,980
Let me ask you three questions.

244
00:10:07,150 --> 00:10:07,910
First,

245
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:09,910
is Mr. Zheng the person

246
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:11,460
that Mrs. Zheng cares most about?

247
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:12,060
Of course.

248
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:12,710
Second,

249
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,390
do you and Mrs. Zheng

250
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,100
talk often?

251
00:10:16,370 --> 00:10:17,030
Not really.

252
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:17,630
Third,

253
00:10:18,130 --> 00:10:19,760
does Mr. Zheng usually

254
00:10:20,030 --> 00:10:21,340
take good care of you?

255
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:25,220
That's exactly the problem.

256
00:10:25,650 --> 00:10:26,380
Listen to me.

257
00:10:27,870 --> 00:10:29,480
The next time you go,

258
00:10:29,740 --> 00:10:30,860
dress a bit more plainly.

259
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:32,220
Don't look too flashy.

260
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:34,530
I look flashy?

261
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:35,550
Me?

262
00:10:35,580 --> 00:10:35,940
No.

263
00:10:36,650 --> 00:10:37,080
No, no, no.

264
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:37,680
No, no, no.

265
00:10:37,790 --> 00:10:39,340
That's not what I mean.

266
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:40,820
What I mean is...

267
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:44,460
You're already

268
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:45,440
very pretty.

269
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:46,500
You...

270
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:48,290
So if you dress up even a little,

271
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:49,360
you just look really,

272
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,420
really beautiful.

273
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:51,790
It's human nature

274
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,770
to be jealous.

275
00:10:53,290 --> 00:10:54,530
Especially since Mrs. Zheng

276
00:10:54,530 --> 00:10:56,190
cares so much about Mr. Zheng.

277
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:56,700
Go on.

278
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,120
Anyway,

279
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:01,130
you need to get closer

280
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:02,770
to Mrs. Zheng.

281
00:11:03,770 --> 00:11:05,510
Even if you want to talk to Mr. Zheng,

282
00:11:05,510 --> 00:11:06,480
you have to go through

283
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,480
Mrs. Zheng first.

284
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:10,030
For a grown man,

285
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:11,760
you sure know a lot about women.

286
00:11:12,550 --> 00:11:14,210
You flirted with a lot of girls

287
00:11:14,650 --> 00:11:16,650
in your salted fish factory, right?

288
00:11:16,980 --> 00:11:18,440
I didn't have to do that.

289
00:11:18,460 --> 00:11:20,790
They all talked to me first.

290
00:11:27,410 --> 00:11:28,510
Anyway, from now on,

291
00:11:28,510 --> 00:11:29,650
if anything happens,

292
00:11:29,650 --> 00:11:30,380
just tell me.

293
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,660
We'll figure it out together.

294
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,370
You said it before.

295
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:38,120
Don't shoulder it all by yourself.

296
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:40,240
It's no big deal. I can handle it.

297
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:43,630
By the way,

298
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:44,980
that Gut Cook

299
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:47,170
hasn't been bothering you lately, has he?

300
00:11:47,170 --> 00:11:47,830
Let him try.

301
00:11:48,220 --> 00:11:50,350
I've still got plenty of pepper spray.

302
00:11:51,170 --> 00:11:51,580
Good.

303
00:11:52,130 --> 00:11:53,530
I have more if you run out.

304
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:59,820
When I first came to Beijing,

305
00:12:00,170 --> 00:12:01,770
I thought this city was huge.

306
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:04,120
Just getting to class takes

307
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:05,460
an hour and a half by bus.

308
00:12:06,170 --> 00:12:07,180
A round trip

309
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:10,160
is enough to circle my hometown twice.

310
00:12:12,910 --> 00:12:13,750
But after Kang Shunyin

311
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:14,750
made such a scene,

312
00:12:16,620 --> 00:12:18,080
I have a new understanding

313
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,450
of Beijing's vastness.

314
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:24,670
Here,

315
00:12:25,790 --> 00:12:27,670
no one cares about your madness

316
00:12:29,010 --> 00:12:30,410
or your joys and sorrows.

317
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,220
Maybe that is

318
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,840
a special kind of tolerance.

319
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:36,680
It's nice.

320
00:12:37,940 --> 00:12:38,740
It feels free.

321
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:40,860
Yeah.

322
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:43,390
In Beijing,

323
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:46,600
no matter how successful you are,

324
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:48,370
this big city

325
00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:49,980
won't think

326
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,000
you're a big deal.

327
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:54,290
If you just want to lie around,

328
00:12:54,290 --> 00:12:54,940
Beijing

329
00:12:55,410 --> 00:12:56,870
won't kick you out either.

330
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,030
No one cares about you here!

331
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:02,360
But everyone asks,

332
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,000
"Have you eaten?"

333
00:13:09,740 --> 00:13:11,360
Whether you're a big shot

334
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:13,410
or a nobody,

335
00:13:15,860 --> 00:13:17,860
don't take yourself too seriously.

336
00:13:17,910 --> 00:13:20,370
But you can't think
you're nothing, either.

337
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:27,340
Right.

338
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,890
Will you stay in Beijing forever?

339
00:13:36,410 --> 00:13:37,080
I hope so.

340
00:13:38,550 --> 00:13:39,840
I hope I can too!

341
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,730
When our temporary residence permits

342
00:13:44,750 --> 00:13:45,740
gets renewed,

343
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:47,680
we'll go get them together!

344
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:07,200
Zongbao,

345
00:14:08,050 --> 00:14:09,100
I originally wanted

346
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:10,320
to come back for a nap.

347
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:12,240
I realized that Li Xiaobo

348
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,170
is acting really shady.

349
00:14:13,170 --> 00:14:15,340
He was secretly handing someone money.

350
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:16,720
He gets up at the crack of dawn too.

351
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:17,860
He doesn't look like someone

352
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:19,080
who does honest work.

353
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:20,180
What do you mean?

354
00:14:20,550 --> 00:14:21,980
Are you saying

355
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,390
he's not a good person?

356
00:14:23,390 --> 00:14:23,820
I...

357
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,150
I met him this morning.

358
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:27,620
He said he went to

359
00:14:27,630 --> 00:14:28,790
buy train tickets.

360
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:29,980
What?

361
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,000
He's a ticket scalper?

362
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:32,600
No, no, no.

363
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:33,600
He said it's for...

364
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,600
He said he's buying for his company.

365
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,980
Alright. Let's keep an eye on him.

366
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,250
He's just not a good person.

367
00:14:45,530 --> 00:14:46,060
Zongbao.

368
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:48,240
Add some more chili peppers.

369
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:48,750
More?

370
00:14:50,010 --> 00:14:50,370
Sure.

371
00:14:50,980 --> 00:14:52,050
No matter how many peppers you add,

372
00:14:52,050 --> 00:14:53,700
it's all just veggies.

373
00:14:53,770 --> 00:14:55,030
Zongbao, make some meat dishes,

374
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:55,620
alright?

375
00:14:55,650 --> 00:14:56,740
These past few days, I...

376
00:14:56,740 --> 00:14:57,630
Where are we gonna get meat?

377
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:58,510
Are you paying?

378
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:00,100
Let's all chip in.

379
00:15:00,630 --> 00:15:02,120
My pants are about to fall off.

380
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:03,130
I want meat too.

381
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:04,130
You're all here?

382
00:15:04,410 --> 00:15:04,770
You're back?

383
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:05,530
Chatting?

384
00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:06,340
Let me see.

385
00:15:06,670 --> 00:15:08,270
What good food are you making?

386
00:15:08,270 --> 00:15:09,460
Stir-frying two veggie dishes.

387
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:10,590
Let's eat together.

388
00:15:11,740 --> 00:15:12,740
That's too plain.

389
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:13,740
For us men,

390
00:15:13,740 --> 00:15:14,980
we can't treat our stomachs poorly.

391
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:16,380
We need some meat dishes.

392
00:15:16,410 --> 00:15:16,790
Just in time.

393
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,320
I'll add a meat dish for you.

394
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:18,790
Look.

395
00:15:19,530 --> 00:15:20,550
Roast chicken.

396
00:15:22,410 --> 00:15:23,360
Sorry about today.

397
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:24,080
It's fine.

398
00:15:24,550 --> 00:15:24,980
Here.

399
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:27,010
Also got a bottle of liquor.

400
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,550
I got up too early.

401
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:29,670
I've been looking for a chance

402
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:31,410
to treat you guys to some food and drink.

403
00:15:31,410 --> 00:15:32,430
Eat the roast chicken while it's hot.

404
00:15:32,430 --> 00:15:33,410
It goes well with your veggie dishes.

405
00:15:33,410 --> 00:15:33,810
Great.

406
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:34,620
Great.

407
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:35,650
You're too kind.

408
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:36,890
No, no. Don't mention it. Come on.

409
00:15:36,890 --> 00:15:37,550
I'll leave this here for you.

410
00:15:37,550 --> 00:15:39,010
We usually drink this too.

411
00:15:39,670 --> 00:15:40,630
I put it on the table for you.

412
00:15:40,630 --> 00:15:41,830
There's more liquor.

413
00:15:41,980 --> 00:15:42,720
Dig in.

414
00:15:42,860 --> 00:15:43,790
-You're too kind.
-Hurry up.

415
00:15:43,790 --> 00:15:44,550
Look at him.

416
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:45,920
So generous.

417
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:48,010
You just follow whoever feeds you.

418
00:15:48,010 --> 00:15:49,070
Then don't eat any.

419
00:15:49,410 --> 00:15:49,910
Stir it.

420
00:15:53,050 --> 00:15:54,250
Why are you in bed?

421
00:15:54,290 --> 00:15:55,380
Come eat with us.

422
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:55,880
No, no.

423
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:57,200
I already ate.

424
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:59,220
I won't stand on ceremony with you.

425
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:00,200
Join us.

426
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:00,630
Eat.

427
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:02,120
I get up too early every day.
I'm sleep-deprived.

428
00:16:02,120 --> 00:16:02,770
I'm going to sleep.

429
00:16:02,770 --> 00:16:03,500
You guys eat.

430
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:04,440
Go to sleep.

431
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:06,740
Pull the blanket up.

432
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:08,700
Cover your stomach.

433
00:16:08,740 --> 00:16:10,270
It's damp in this basement.

434
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,480
You sleep. Sleep.

435
00:16:12,620 --> 00:16:13,350
Thanks, bro.

436
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,430
You're welcome.

437
00:16:18,130 --> 00:16:19,150
Well, this...

438
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:19,960
I'll...

439
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:21,980
mix some dipping sauce.

440
00:16:22,170 --> 00:16:23,550
And shred the chicken.

441
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:24,480
Okay.

442
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:31,010
Zongbao.

443
00:16:31,270 --> 00:16:31,720
What?

444
00:16:32,820 --> 00:16:33,510
I think

445
00:16:33,740 --> 00:16:35,410
he just wants to use roast chicken

446
00:16:35,410 --> 00:16:36,140
to shut us up.

447
00:16:38,170 --> 00:16:39,320
I'll mix some more sauce

448
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,370
to open

449
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:41,480
your mouth.

450
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:44,150
Whether my mouth's open or shut,

451
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:45,500
it won't stop

452
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:46,630
my suspicion of him.

453
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:48,720
What are you suspicious of?

454
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:50,500
Always suspicious of this and that.

455
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:51,500
You suspect anyone

456
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:52,910
that walks into Room 108,

457
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:54,130
just like how

458
00:16:54,460 --> 00:16:56,410
you treated Xu Shengli back then.

459
00:16:56,730 --> 00:16:57,670
No, about Shengli...

460
00:16:57,670 --> 00:16:58,200
Shengli!

461
00:16:58,410 --> 00:17:00,210
Where are you going? Not eating?

462
00:17:00,910 --> 00:17:01,440
Shengli.

463
00:17:02,860 --> 00:17:03,320
This...

464
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:08,480
MSG.

465
00:17:16,790 --> 00:17:17,960
I'm not eating either, Zongbao.

466
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:19,069
What? Why aren't you eating?

467
00:17:19,069 --> 00:17:20,660
I just finished mixing the sauce.

468
00:17:20,660 --> 00:17:22,660
Even roast chicken can't shut me up.

469
00:17:26,220 --> 00:17:26,619
Great.

470
00:17:29,850 --> 00:17:30,780
Not eating, huh?

471
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:35,680
I'll eat the chicken myself.

472
00:17:40,510 --> 00:17:40,970
This...

473
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,380
This isn't roast chicken.

474
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:45,980
It's a specimen.

475
00:17:49,330 --> 00:17:50,010
It's okay.

476
00:17:50,350 --> 00:17:51,950
If not, I can just borrow one.

477
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:54,680
No rush.

478
00:17:56,530 --> 00:17:57,730
You're the best, Mom.

479
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:02,000
I'm hanging up.

480
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,060
Hello, Yan.

481
00:18:16,310 --> 00:18:17,680
I have a favor to ask you.

482
00:18:18,830 --> 00:18:19,740
Do you have

483
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:21,070
a spare sewing machine?

484
00:18:23,110 --> 00:18:24,270
Could I borrow it for a few days?

485
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:25,220
I want to alter

486
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:26,400
some clothes later.

487
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:28,650
Thanks, Yan.

488
00:18:29,420 --> 00:18:29,750
Okay.

489
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:34,900
Done.

490
00:18:39,090 --> 00:18:40,820
You didn't go to Mr. He's place?

491
00:18:42,050 --> 00:18:43,480
I haven't finished the task

492
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:44,660
he assigned me.

493
00:18:44,810 --> 00:18:46,670
Then why don't you hurry up and go?

494
00:18:47,380 --> 00:18:49,140
Five minutes won't make a difference.

495
00:18:49,140 --> 00:18:49,900
Look who's talking.

496
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:50,610
It's Friday.

497
00:18:50,610 --> 00:18:52,070
Didn't you skip class too?

498
00:18:52,510 --> 00:18:53,030
Me?

499
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:55,310
I wanted to practice on my own
at home today.

500
00:18:55,310 --> 00:18:56,370
Is there a problem?

501
00:18:56,790 --> 00:18:58,220
Practicing at home alone

502
00:18:58,250 --> 00:19:01,000
isn't as good as practicing
at the teacher's home.

503
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,030
When it comes to singing,

504
00:19:02,030 --> 00:19:03,400
you think you know more than I do?

505
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,770
Are you not going

506
00:19:04,790 --> 00:19:05,880
because of the money?

507
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:06,680
Of course not.

508
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:09,400
Don't worry

509
00:19:10,740 --> 00:19:11,670
about the money.

510
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:13,700
What? I don't want it.

511
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:15,830
Just open it and see.

512
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:16,960
No.

513
00:19:18,010 --> 00:19:18,830
Open it.

514
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:30,070
A drumstick?

515
00:19:30,850 --> 00:19:31,460
Where did you get this?

516
00:19:31,460 --> 00:19:32,290
Don't worry about that.

517
00:19:32,290 --> 00:19:34,690
Do you know more about chicken legs
than me?

518
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:40,820
Why aren't you eating it?

519
00:19:41,090 --> 00:19:42,690
I'll enjoy it when I get back.

520
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:47,320
Did you eat?

521
00:19:47,380 --> 00:19:47,740
I did.

522
00:19:48,070 --> 00:19:49,740
I ate the other drumstick.

523
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:52,480
Thanks.

524
00:19:52,530 --> 00:19:53,460
You're welcome.

525
00:19:58,140 --> 00:19:58,920
The noodles are ready.

526
00:19:58,920 --> 00:19:59,580
Come and eat

527
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:00,830
before it gets clumpy.

528
00:20:00,830 --> 00:20:01,400
Coming.

529
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,110
Smells good.

530
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:04,530
Look.

531
00:20:08,550 --> 00:20:09,740
A drumstick?

532
00:20:17,270 --> 00:20:18,810
I have one too.

533
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:22,960
You eat yours, I'll eat mine.

534
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:24,000
We'll each eat our own.

535
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:24,480
Okay.

536
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:26,310
One for each of us.

537
00:20:28,180 --> 00:20:29,180
It smells so good.

538
00:20:30,180 --> 00:20:32,040
Be careful, it's hot. Eat slowly.

539
00:20:33,810 --> 00:20:34,670
Is it too bland?

540
00:20:34,850 --> 00:20:35,570
It's just right.

541
00:20:35,570 --> 00:20:37,290
Your throat can't handle
salty food anyway.

542
00:20:37,290 --> 00:20:38,150
So thoughtful.

543
00:20:39,420 --> 00:20:40,020
By the way,

544
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:42,460
You practice singing every day.

545
00:20:42,460 --> 00:20:43,920
Can your throat take it?

546
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:44,780
It's okay.

547
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:48,550
But usually,

548
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:50,350
I do need to take care of my voice.

549
00:20:51,270 --> 00:20:52,670
Liangliang told me today

550
00:20:53,010 --> 00:20:55,140
that their bar is looking for a singer.

551
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:56,440
Do you want to give it a try?

552
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:58,440
You can practice and make money too.

553
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:01,770
They're hiring pop singers,
aren't they?

554
00:21:04,220 --> 00:21:06,020
Singing folk songs and pop songs

555
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:07,360
are quite different.

556
00:21:08,090 --> 00:21:09,200
If I sing too much pop,

557
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:09,850
my vocal placement

558
00:21:09,850 --> 00:21:11,050
could easily change.

559
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,800
What if you switch to pop?

560
00:21:13,010 --> 00:21:13,440
Look,

561
00:21:13,590 --> 00:21:14,500
so many stars

562
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:15,530
sing pop.

563
00:21:16,050 --> 00:21:17,650
They get both money and fame.

564
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:24,960
But singing folk songs

565
00:21:25,420 --> 00:21:26,240
and joining the troupe

566
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:27,570
is why I came to Beijing.

567
00:21:28,830 --> 00:21:30,490
I can't give up just for money.

568
00:21:30,900 --> 00:21:32,470
What will you do if you can't

569
00:21:32,510 --> 00:21:33,640
get into the troupe?

570
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:36,070
Then what if no one

571
00:21:36,090 --> 00:21:37,020
hires you to act?

572
00:21:37,550 --> 00:21:38,770
Then I'll keep going until the end.

573
00:21:38,770 --> 00:21:39,460
I don't believe

574
00:21:39,460 --> 00:21:40,610
no one will ever hire me.

575
00:21:40,610 --> 00:21:41,420
Me too.

576
00:21:47,380 --> 00:21:48,440
Eat the drumstick.

577
00:21:52,050 --> 00:21:52,510
Come on.

578
00:21:52,790 --> 00:21:54,190
Cheers with drumsticks.

579
00:21:56,850 --> 00:21:58,330
-It's so good.
-So good.

580
00:22:10,510 --> 00:22:12,640
Have a drumstick to cool off.

581
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,010
Never heard of that.

582
00:22:16,270 --> 00:22:17,750
A friend of mine said,

583
00:22:18,350 --> 00:22:20,410
"Eating well keeps the temper down."

584
00:22:20,770 --> 00:22:21,570
I bought these erjingtiao peppers

585
00:22:21,570 --> 00:22:22,700
early this morning.

586
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:25,250
I didn't dare overcook them
for even a second.

587
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:26,480
Who did you

588
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:29,010
learn this from?

589
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:29,900
A friend...

590
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:31,380
of a friend.

591
00:22:32,740 --> 00:22:33,770
I mean,

592
00:22:34,740 --> 00:22:35,670
who did you learn

593
00:22:36,310 --> 00:22:38,220
your sweet-talking tricks

594
00:22:38,570 --> 00:22:39,750
from?

595
00:22:40,010 --> 00:22:41,480
Then I'll tell you the truth.

596
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:42,420
I learned it from

597
00:22:42,940 --> 00:22:44,870
"The Legend of the Condor Heroes."

598
00:22:47,420 --> 00:22:49,350
You're treating me as Hong Qigong?

599
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,660
You cook a meal,

600
00:22:51,070 --> 00:22:52,200
buy a roast chicken,

601
00:22:53,460 --> 00:22:54,330
and think you've won me over?

602
00:22:54,330 --> 00:22:55,930
It's not just roast chicken.

603
00:22:59,380 --> 00:23:00,440
There's also this.

604
00:23:01,530 --> 00:23:02,510
You know me.

605
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:04,510
I speak before I think.

606
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:07,160
Words go in my ears,

607
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:08,820
and I don't digest them first.

608
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:10,180
But the most important thing

609
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:11,570
is... is that I broke the rules.

610
00:23:11,570 --> 00:23:13,030
You said I wasn't allowed to
touch anything,

611
00:23:13,030 --> 00:23:14,070
but I... I still touched

612
00:23:14,070 --> 00:23:15,610
your most important things.

613
00:23:15,610 --> 00:23:16,110
Your

614
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:17,390
creative ideas,

615
00:23:17,530 --> 00:23:18,220
your words,

616
00:23:18,790 --> 00:23:19,990
and your characters.

617
00:23:23,030 --> 00:23:23,880
Take this.

618
00:23:24,940 --> 00:23:26,200
In the future, if anyone here

619
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,510
doesn't follow the rules,

620
00:23:27,510 --> 00:23:29,310
you can beat them without worry.

621
00:23:48,420 --> 00:23:48,950
How is it?

622
00:23:49,830 --> 00:23:50,430
Is it okay?

623
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:52,900
To call it authentic

624
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:55,400
would be flattery.

625
00:23:56,350 --> 00:23:57,810
This Sichuan dish of yours

626
00:23:58,050 --> 00:23:59,510
has the form

627
00:24:00,790 --> 00:24:03,550
but lacks the spirit of Sichuan cuisine.

628
00:24:04,310 --> 00:24:05,040
Understood.

629
00:24:05,570 --> 00:24:07,850
I'll strive for both form
and spirit next time.

630
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:08,720
You kid.

631
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,030
You're so scheming.

632
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,510
Don't say that.

633
00:24:16,030 --> 00:24:17,000
If you eat well,

634
00:24:17,290 --> 00:24:18,620
you'll be in a good mood.

635
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:20,250
If you're in a good mood,

636
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:22,140
inspiration will flow like a spring.

637
00:24:22,140 --> 00:24:23,030
Then won't your writing

638
00:24:23,030 --> 00:24:24,290
get better and better?

639
00:24:31,270 --> 00:24:32,800
This dog-beating stick...

640
00:24:34,070 --> 00:24:35,070
feels handy.

641
00:24:35,610 --> 00:24:37,090
It's just a stick.

642
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:38,720
It's not a dog-beating stick.

643
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:39,780
I don't hit people.

644
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:41,610
I only beat dogs.

645
00:24:42,750 --> 00:24:43,850
The logic at this point

646
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:44,940
has to be written like this.

647
00:24:44,940 --> 00:24:45,980
Say that again.

648
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:47,570
It has to be written like this

649
00:24:47,570 --> 00:24:48,300
at this part.

650
00:24:48,420 --> 00:24:48,880
Okay.

651
00:24:49,180 --> 00:24:50,840
Shut the door and beat the dog!

652
00:24:51,590 --> 00:24:52,320
Beat the dog.

653
00:24:52,530 --> 00:24:53,530
I'll beat the dog.

654
00:24:53,660 --> 00:24:55,720
-Beat me... You can't catch me!
-I will.

655
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:56,180
I'll hit you.

656
00:24:56,180 --> 00:24:56,680
Come on.

657
00:24:57,180 --> 00:24:58,180
I'll beat the dog.

658
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:00,040
Come here.

659
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:00,960
Get over here.

660
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:02,020
Come here.

661
00:25:02,350 --> 00:25:02,950
Come here.

662
00:25:03,090 --> 00:25:04,090
Don't be angry.

663
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,000
Give it to me.

664
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:05,700
I'll let you hit me.

665
00:25:05,700 --> 00:25:06,790
-Give it to me!
-I'll let you hit me.

666
00:25:06,790 --> 00:25:07,400
Give it to me!

667
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:08,030
I'll let you hit me.

668
00:25:08,030 --> 00:25:09,160
Hit me. Go on.

669
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:10,070
Master, hit me.

670
00:25:11,220 --> 00:25:12,880
Master, hit me.

671
00:25:15,550 --> 00:25:16,010
Okay.

672
00:25:16,940 --> 00:25:17,740
Keep writing.

673
00:25:18,660 --> 00:25:19,460
Keep writing.

674
00:26:00,330 --> 00:26:00,990
Mrs. Zheng,

675
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:02,550
from now on,

676
00:26:02,550 --> 00:26:03,530
I'll come a bit early before class.

677
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:04,330
If you need help

678
00:26:04,330 --> 00:26:05,250
